1  BBS Support
2 
3  Filling out and returning the enclosed
4  registration card will entitle you to
5  free TeleWar revisions and updates
6  (should any be necessary), accessible
7  as downloads on our 2400 baud bulletin
8  board, Track ][. Phone # (817) 244-4151.
9  When we receive your registration card,
10 you will be logged in as a registered
11 TeleWar user.
12
13 We would also ask that you report any
14 problems you might be having with
15 TeleWar in the BBS message area. Any
16 inquiries made will usually be answered
17 within 24 hours.
18
19 Although a great deal of testing has
20 gone into TeleWar to insure that it is
21 bug free, we realize that no software
22 can ever be called "finished". Every
23 effort has been made to prevent the user
24 from accidentally causing a program
25 error between teleconnected computers.
26 However, this does not mean purposeful
27 attempts to misuse the software will not
28 result in a disconnected or mismatched
29 game displays. Be deliberate with your
30 mouse or keyboard inputs and everything
31 will work as expected. With any quality
32 software, used correctly, it will
33 function correctly.
34
35 It would also be a great help to us, if
36 you would save the game at the point
37 where the problem occurred.  Then upload
38 the saved game file to us in the 
39 TeleGames File area on Track ][.
40
41 Please leave a post in the message area
42 listing the type of computer you are
43 using and the problem you are having.

                 Page 4


1  Our BBS is also a great place to meet
2  other TeleWar users interested in
3  playing TeleWar (or TeleGames). Post
4  from TeleWar users issuing game
5  challenges may be found in the Track ][
6  TeleGames message area.
